title: What does this mean?
body:
Either I don't speak English or this makes no sense...

[IMAGE](http://imgur.com/a/zk2Ie)

I can be put in a position that's not one of the two I chose if I don't support/fill???

replies.body:
It means that you're garenteed to be one of your two preferred positions, because you were recently placed in a "Fill" or "Support" position. So say, for example, you're preferred positions are Top and Mid, you'd be garenteed to get either Top or Mid, meaning you *wouldn't* get Jungle, "Marksman" or Support.

It seems to be pretty self-explanatory to me, maybe you're just not thinking straight at the moment.
I believe he was simply unaware of autofill existing, he probably has never encountered it before.
I have never had autofill happen to me, even if I pick mid/top/jungle.
Doesn't happen to everyone, depends what level of play you're at, and how many people are playing at that time. I'm supp/mid main so I've never been autofilled either.

When "autofill" is on you can be put in to any role.

Autofill is usually turned on when the que times are really long.

By queing FIll or playing Support, you become immune to "autofill" for a short period of games.
